abstract: Iran will respond forcefully to any Israeli action against its interests in the region, Iran's Foreign Ministry said on Wednesday, according to the Mehr news agency.
snippet: Iran will respond forcefully to any Israeli action against its interests in the region, Iran's Foreign Ministry said on Wednesday, according to the Mehr news agency.
lead_paragraph: DUBAI — Iran will respond forcefully to any Israeli action against its interests in the region, Iran's Foreign Ministry said on Wednesday, according to the Mehr news agency.
headline_main: Iran Vows 'Crushing Response' to Any Israeli Action Against Regional Interests
headline_print_headline: Iran Vows 'Crushing Response' to Any Israeli Action Against Regional Interests

abstract: A Florida jury acquitted a Chinese woman Wednesday of trespassing at President Donald Trump's Mar-a-Lago resort after she testified she didn't understand a security guard who told her to leave.
snippet: A Florida jury acquitted a Chinese woman Wednesday of trespassing at President Donald Trump's Mar-a-Lago resort after she testified she didn't understand a security guard who told her to leave.
lead_paragraph: WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. — A Florida jury acquitted a Chinese woman Wednesday of trespassing at President Donald Trump's Mar-a-Lago resort after she testified she didn't understand a security guard who told her to leave.
headline_main: Jury Finds Mar-a-Lago Intruder Not Guilty of Trespassing
headline_print_headline: Jury Finds Mar-a-Lago Intruder Not Guilty of Trespassing

abstract: Republican members of the U.S. House of Representatives Intelligence Committee refused to attend a subcommittee hearing on technology and national security on Wednesday, boycotting the panel's first public hearing since the acrimonious impeachment inquiry into President Donald Trump.
snippet: Republican members of the U.S. House of Representatives Intelligence Committee refused to attend a subcommittee hearing on technology and national security on Wednesday, boycotting the panel's first public hearing since the acrimonious impeachment...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Republican members of the U.S. House of Representatives Intelligence Committee refused to attend a subcommittee hearing on technology and national security on Wednesday, boycotting the panel's first public hearing since the acrimonious impeachment inquiry into President Donald Trump.
headline_main: In Wake of Impeachment, Trump Allies Boycott House Intelligence Tech Hearing
headline_print_headline: In Wake of Impeachment, Trump Allies Boycott House Intelligence Tech Hearing

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump on Wednesday signed an executive order directing U.S. agencies to test the vulnerabilities of critical infrastructure systems in the event of a disruption or manipulation of satellite-based global positioning system services (GPS).
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump on Wednesday signed an executive order directing U.S. agencies to test the vulnerabilities of critical infrastructure systems in the event of a disruption or manipulation of satellite-based global positioning system ser...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump on Wednesday signed an executive order directing U.S. agencies to test the vulnerabilities of critical infrastructure systems in the event of a disruption or manipulation of satellite-based global positioning system services (GPS).
headline_main: Trump Signs Order to Test U.S. Infrastructure's Vulnerability to GPS Outage
headline_print_headline: Trump Signs Order to Test U.S. Infrastructure's Vulnerability to GPS Outage

abstract: Two senators — one Republican and one Democrat — are leading a legislative effort to have a global women's initiative spearheaded by President Donald Trump's daughter Ivanka written into law.
snippet: Two senators — one Republican and one Democrat — are leading a legislative effort to have a global women's initiative spearheaded by President Donald Trump's daughter Ivanka written into law.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Two senators — one Republican and one Democrat — are leading a legislative effort to have a global women's initiative spearheaded by President Donald Trump's daughter Ivanka written into law.
headline_main: Lawmakers Want Ivanka Trump's Women's Program to Become Law
headline_print_headline: Lawmakers Want Ivanka Trump's Women's Program to Become Law

abstract: The United Nations' human rights office on Wednesday named 112 companies it said have business ties to Jewish settlements in the West Bank, angering Israel and prompting a Palestinian threat of legal action against the firms.
snippet: The United Nations' human rights office on Wednesday named 112 companies it said have business ties to Jewish settlements in the West Bank, angering Israel and prompting a Palestinian threat of legal action against the firms.
lead_paragraph: GENEVA — The United Nations' human rights office on Wednesday named 112 companies it said have business ties to Jewish settlements in the West Bank, angering Israel and prompting a Palestinian threat of legal action against the firms.
headline_main: U.N. Report Names 112 Companies Doing Business With Israeli Settlements
headline_print_headline: U.N. Report Names 112 Companies Doing Business With Israeli Settlements

abstract: U.S. presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg on Wednesday won endorsements from three Congressional Black Caucus members, a positive sign for his campaign, which has drawn scrutiny lately over his past support for a controversial policing tactic.
snippet: U.S. presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg on Wednesday won endorsements from three Congressional Black Caucus members, a positive sign for his campaign, which has drawn scrutiny lately over his past support for a controversial policing tactic.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg on Wednesday won endorsements from three Congressional Black Caucus members, a positive sign for his campaign, which has drawn scrutiny lately over his past support for a controversial policing tactic.
headline_main: U.S. Presidential Candidate Bloomberg Endorsed by Three Black Lawmakers
headline_print_headline: U.S. Presidential Candidate Bloomberg Endorsed by Three Black Lawmakers

abstract: New York's governor plans to propose to President Donald Trump that the state could share some driving records with federal immigration agencies if the administration reverses its move to block state residents from Global Entry and other programs that allow travelers to avoid long border security lines.
snippet: New York's governor plans to propose to President Donald Trump that the state could share some driving records with federal immigration agencies if the administration reverses its move to block state residents from Global Entry and other programs ...
lead_paragraph: ALBANY, N.Y. — New York's governor plans to propose to President Donald Trump that the state could share some driving records with federal immigration agencies if the administration reverses its move to block state residents from Global Entry and other programs that allow travelers to avoid long border security lines.
headline_main: Cuomo to Propose Compromise, Hopes to End Global Entry Ban
headline_print_headline: Cuomo to Propose Compromise, Hopes to End Global Entry Ban
